        <div class="article">
            <div class="paragraph">
                <p>A few years ago by crossing Middle East airspace I experienced my most beautiful flight. 
                    I have never liked to fly, I have always tried to fall asleep quickly to wake up at my destination, 
                    but at that time I spent hours looking at the moonlit night. Until a moment I saw countless of bright 
                    flames far, far away but still visible. Like a dozens of bonfires. I realized that they could not be bonfires, 
                    they would not be visible from the plane and they were many. What is it, where, why? What a magical night! </p>

                <p> Only this year, when I arrived in Qatar and saw the flaming oil towers I realized that perhaps these "bonfires" 
                    in my nightly covered world were my first meeting with Qatar. A land that now has a special place in my heart. 
                    I have found you - my flaming desert pearl.</p>
            </div>
